# System Requirements

## Functional Requirements

### Customer Management

The system shall:

- Allow customers to create an account.
- Allow customers to update their personal information.
- Allow customers to view their profile.
- Allow business staff to search for customers.
- Allow business staff to update customer records.
- Allow business staff to deactivate customer accounts.

### Pet Management

The system shall:

- Allow customers to register one or more pets.
- Store pet information including name, breed, age, weight, and grooming notes.
- Allow customers to edit pet information.
- Allow business staff to update pet records.
- Associate each pet with a customer.

### Appointment Management

The system shall:

- Allow customers to schedule appointments.
- Allow customers to cancel appointments.
- Allow customers to reschedule appointments.
- Allow business staff to view daily appointments.
- Prevent appointment conflicts.
- Associate appointments with customers, pets, and services.

### Service Management

The system shall:

- Display available grooming services.
- Display pricing information.
- Allow business staff to add new services.
- Allow business staff to edit services.
- Allow business staff to deactivate services.

### Employee Management

The system shall:

- Store employee information.
- Assign appointments to employees.
- Allow business staff to manage employee records.

### Contact & Employment

The system shall:

- Display business contact information.
- Provide a contact form.
- Allow applicants to submit employment applications.

---

## Non-Functional Requirements

### Security

The system shall:

- Require authentication for administrative functions.
- Protect sensitive customer information.
- Validate user input.

### Performance

The system shall:

- Respond to user requests within an acceptable time.
- Support multiple users simultaneously.

### Reliability

The system shall:

- Preserve stored customer information.
- Recover gracefully from unexpected errors.

### Usability

The system shall:

- Provide an intuitive interface.
- Be responsive across desktop and mobile devices.

### Maintainability

The system shall:

- Be organized using modular software architecture.
- Follow clean coding practices.
- Be documented to support future development.

### Scalability

The system shall:

- Support future business growth.
- Allow additional features to be integrated without major redesign.
